{"title_page": "Latania lontaroides", "text_new": "{{Speciesbox\n| image = Latanier-rouge-Mascarin.jpg\n| status = EN\n| status_system = IUCN2.3\n| status_ref = <ref name=iucn/>\n| genus = Latania\n| species = lontaroides\n| authority = (Gaertner) H.E.Moore\n| synonyms = *''Cleophora commersonii''<small> (J.F.Gmel.) O.F.Cook</small>\n*''Cleophora lontaroides''<small> Gaertn.</small>\n*''Latania borbonica''<small> Lam.</small>\n*''Latania commersonii''<small> J.F.Gmel.</small>\n*''Latania rubra''<small> Jacq.</small>\n| synonyms_ref = <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theplantlist.org/tpl/record/kew-108912 |title=''Latania lontaroides'' (Gaertn.) H.E.Moore |publisher=The Plant List |accessdate=21 December 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Latania lontaroides''''' is a species of [[arecaceae|palm tree]]. It is [[endemism|endemic]] to [[R\u00e9union]]. It is also used as an [[ornamental plant]]. Its common names include '''''latanier de la R\u00e9union''''' and '''''latanier rouge'''''.<ref name=iucn>Johnson, D. 1998. [http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/38589/0 ''Latania lontaroides''.] The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2015.2. Downloaded on 08 September 2015.</ref> The [[Diaspididae|armored scale insect]] ''[[Hemiberlesia lataniae]]'' was [[Species description|first described]] from this species of palm, and has since spread around the world and proved to be a serious pest of [[avocado]].<ref name=Sharp>{{cite book|author1=Pe\u00f1a, Jorge E. |author2=Sharp, Jennifer L.|author3=Wysoki, M.|title=Tropical Fruit Pests and Pollinators: Biology, Economic Importance, Natural Enemies, and Control|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=t_BSs0hrAPAC&pg=PA234 |year=2002 |publisher=CABI |isbn=978-0-85199-976-0 |page=234}}</ref>\n\nThis palm was common on R\u00e9union at one time, but the area in which it grows has diminished as land has been cleared for agriculture and for other purposes. The [[International Union for Conservation of Nature]] has assessed it as being an [[endangered species]] in the wild, however it is also grown as an ornamental plant in various parts of the world.<ref name=iucn/>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Latanialontaroides.JPG|Form\nFile:Latania lontaroides young foliage (detail).JPG|Leaf\nFile:Lantania lontariodes.jpg|One of the few remaining in the wild in [[La Possession]] (male)\n</gallery>\nFile:/Users/rubenpena/Desktop/IMG_0533.jpeg\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q1348304}}\n\n[[Category:Latania|lontaroides]]\n[[Category:Endemic flora of R\u00e9union]]\n[[Category:Palms of R\u00e9union]]\n[[Category:Endangered plants]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n\n\n{{R\u00e9union-stub}}\n{{palm-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Speciesbox\n| image = Latanier-rouge-Mascarin.jpg\n| status = EN\n| status_system = IUCN2.3\n| status_ref = <ref name=iucn/>\n| genus = Latania\n| species = lontaroides\n| authority = (Gaertner) H.E.Moore\n| synonyms = *''Cleophora commersonii''<small> (J.F.Gmel.) O.F.Cook</small>\n*''Cleophora lontaroides''<small> Gaertn.</small>\n*''Latania borbonica''<small> Lam.</small>\n*''Latania commersonii''<small> J.F.Gmel.</small>\n*''Latania rubra''<small> Jacq.</small>\n| synonyms_ref = <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theplantlist.org/tpl/record/kew-108912 |title=''Latania lontaroides'' (Gaertn.) H.E.Moore |publisher=The Plant List |accessdate=21 December 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Latania lontaroides''''' is a species of [[arecaceae|palm tree]]. It is [[endemism|endemic]] to [[R\u00e9union]]. It is also used as an [[ornamental plant]]. Its common names include '''''latanier de la R\u00e9union''''' and '''''latanier rouge'''''.<ref name=iucn>Johnson, D. 1998. [http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/38589/0 ''Latania lontaroides''.] The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2015.2. Downloaded on 08 September 2015.</ref> The [[Diaspididae|armored scale insect]] ''[[Hemiberlesia lataniae]]'' was [[Species description|first described]] from this species of palm, and has since spread around the world and proved to be a serious pest of [[avocado]].<ref name=Sharp>{{cite book|author1=Pe\u00f1a, Jorge E. |author2=Sharp, Jennifer L.|author3=Wysoki, M.|title=Tropical Fruit Pests and Pollinators: Biology, Economic Importance, Natural Enemies, and Control|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=t_BSs0hrAPAC&pg=PA234 |year=2002 |publisher=CABI |isbn=978-0-85199-976-0 |page=234}}</ref>\n\nThis palm was common on R\u00e9union at one time, but the area in which it grows has diminished as land has been cleared for agriculture and for other purposes. The [[International Union for Conservation of Nature]] has assessed it as being an [[endangered species]] in the wild, however it is also grown as an ornamental plant in various parts of the world.<ref name=iucn/>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Latanialontaroides.JPG|Form\nFile:Latania lontaroides young foliage (detail).JPG|Leaf\nFile:Lantania lontariodes.jpg|One of the few remaining in the wild in [[La Possession]] (male)\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q1348304}}\n\n[[Category:Latania|lontaroides]]\n[[Category:Endemic flora of R\u00e9union]]\n[[Category:Palms of R\u00e9union]]\n[[Category:Endangered plants]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n\n\n{{R\u00e9union-stub}}\n{{palm-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Therubenpena", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eGallery", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latania_lontaroides"}
{"title_page": "Alexander Dynkin", "text_new": "'''Alexander A. Dynkin''' is a [[Russia]]n economist whose research interests and publications have been in growth, forecasting, international comparisons, technological innovation and energy studies. He is the President of the [[Institute of World Economy and International Relations|''Institute of World Economy and International Relations'' (IMEMO)]] ([[Russian Academy of Sciences|Russian Academy of Science]]) <ref name=\"IMEMO\">http://www.imemo.ru/en/struct/director.php {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101222154411/http://www.imemo.ru/en/struct/director.php |date=2010-12-22 }} Institute of World Economy and International Relations: Brief biography of Alexander A. Dynkin (Accessed Jan 2011)</ref>\n\n== Notability ==\n* Elected for life as a full member of the [[Russian Academy of Sciences|Russian Academy of Science]]<ref name=\"IMEMO\"/>\n* Economic adviser to [[Prime Minister of Russia|Prime-Minister of Russia]] (1998-1999)<ref name=\"IMEMO\"/>\n* 1986 Order of the ''Sign of Worship'' <ref name=\"IMEMO\"/>\n* 2006 ''Friendship Order''<ref name=\"IMEMO\"/>\n* Keynote Speech at UNIDO's Proceedings of the Industrial Development, Forum and Associated Round Tables, [[Vienna]]<ref>[http://capacity4dev.eu/c4d-lib/system/files/document/2010-05-20/The_role_of_industrial_development_in_achievement_of_MDGs.pdf Unido (2003) The Role of Industrial Development in the Achievement of the Millennium Development Goals, Proceedings of the Industrial Development, Forum and Associated Round Tables, Vienna, 1-3 December (p396)]{{Dead link|date=October 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.imemo.ru 'Institute of World Economy and International Relations]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dynkin, Alexander A.}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Moscow Aviation Institute alumni]]\n[[Category:Russian economists]]\n[[Category:Full Members of the Russian Academy of Sciences]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "'''Alexander A. Dynkin''' is a [[Russia]]n economist whose research interests and publications have been in growth, forecasting, international comparisons, technological innovation and energy studies. He is the President of the [[Institute of World Economy and International Relations|''Institute of World Economy and International Relations'' (IMEMO)]] ([[Russian Academy of Sciences|Russian Academy of Science]]) <ref name=\"IMEMO\">http://www.imemo.ru/en/struct/director.php {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101222154411/http://www.imemo.ru/en/struct/director.php |date=2010-12-22 }} Institute of World Economy and International Relations: Brief biography of Alexander A. Dynkin (Accessed Jan 2011)</ref>\n\n== Notability ==\n* Elected for life as a full member of the [[Russian Academy of Sciences|Russian Academy of Science]]<ref name=\"IMEMO\"/>\n* Economic adviser to [[Prime Minister of Russia|Prime-Minister of Russia]] (1998-1999)<ref name=\"IMEMO\"/>\n* 1986 Order of the ''Sign of Worship'' <ref name=\"IMEMO\"/>\n* 2006 ''Friendship Order''<ref name=\"IMEMO\"/>\n* Keynote Speech at UNIDO's Proceedings of the Industrial Development, Forum and Associated Round Tables, [[Vienna]]<ref>[http://capacity4dev.eu/c4d-lib/system/files/document/2010-05-20/The_role_of_industrial_development_in_achievement_of_MDGs.pdf Unido (2003) The Role of Industrial Development in the Achievement of the Millennium Development Goals, Proceedings of the Industrial Development, Forum and Associated Round Tables, Vienna, 1-3 December (p396)]{{Dead link|date=October 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.imemo.ru 'Institute of World Economy and International Relations]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dynkin, Alexander A.}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Moscow Aviation Institute alumni]]\n